    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STOPMASTER WEDGE TYPE BRAKE - INSTALL - SPRING BRAKE CHAMBER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SPRING BRAKE CHAMBER</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble spring brake chamber (collet (lock) nut loose) until it bottoms in the actuator
                housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the collet (lock) nut finger-tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen service chamber clamp to align pressure housing port to proper location.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Retighten service chamber clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 100 psi to service chamber.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten collet (lock) nut 1-1/2 teeth or 125 ft-lbs. (170 N&#8226;m) minimum.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check chamber for air leaks using soap and water solution.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
